Introduction
Advanced Stock Portfolio Tracker is a Python console-based project that allows users to manage their stock investments. It is designed to be simple, practical, and beginner-friendly while still showing multiple important Python concepts.

The project allows users to buy stocks, sell stocks, view their current portfolio, check transaction history, search stock prices, and generate a portfolio report.

Main Purpose
The main purpose of this project is to calculate and track the total value of a stock portfolio.

Instead of only calculating total investment once, this advanced version stores data permanently using CSV files and allows users to manage their portfolio over multiple runs.

How It Works
The program starts with a menu.
The user selects an option from 1 to 8.
The user can view available stocks, buy stock, sell stock, view portfolio, check transaction history, search price, generate report, or exit.
Portfolio data is stored in portfolio.csv.
Buy and sell records are stored in transactions.csv.
A detailed report can be generated in portfolio_report.txt.
Important Python Concepts Used
1. Dictionary
The stock prices are stored in a dictionary.

2. CSV File Handling
CSV files are used to store portfolio and transaction data permanently.

3. Functions
The project is divided into separate functions to make the code clean and easy to understand.

4. Loops
A while loop is used to keep showing the menu until the user exits.

5. Conditional Statements
If-elif-else statements are used to process user choices.

6. Input Validation
The program checks invalid stock symbols, invalid quantities, and wrong menu options.

7. DateTime
The datetime module is used to record transaction date and report generation time.

